===Etymology===
From Late Latin [[anacoluthon]], from Greek [[ανακολουθον]] ‘without sequence’, from [[α-]] + [[ακολουθος]] ‘following’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ænəkə'lu:θɒn/

===Noun===
'''anacoluthon'''
# a [[sentence]] or other structure with no [[grammatical]] sequence; especially when deliberate, as a [[rhetorical]] device